{
  "uuid": "a22fd6d9e7e008d32a523ecea211a2e9",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Sales Agent",
  "description": "<p>📞 Client Experience & Lead Management Executive (Healthcare | Front Desk | Call & WhatsApp Management)</p><p>Heartland Rehab is a growing group of physiotherapy and allied-health clinics across Singapore. We’re looking for a calm, confident, and people-oriented individual to manage all incoming enquiries and leads across our platforms. If you enjoy speaking with people, helping them take the next step, and working in a structured environment — this role is for you.</p><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Respond promptly and professionally as the first point of contact for patients and enquiries across phone calls, WhatsApp, website enquiries, online promotions, and referrals</li><li>Guide clients by explaining available services clearly and assist them in booking appointments accurately</li><li>Follow up with clients on enquiries and self-booking links to ensure engagement and appointment confirmation</li><li>Coordinate with therapists and internal teams to schedule appointments and resolve client needs efficiently</li><li>Maintain detailed records of client interactions and lead management activities following established processes and SOPs</li><li>Manage multiple enquiries simultaneously while maintaining a calm and professional demeanor</li><li>Deliver a smooth, professional client experience from initial contact through appointment booking and follow-up</li></ul><p><strong>Required competencies and certifications</strong></p><p>[None specified in original JD]</p><p><strong>Preferred competencies and qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Experience in healthcare or call-centre environments (training will be provided)</li><li>Strong communication skills for phone and WhatsApp interactions</li><li>Detail-oriented and organized approach to managing enquiries and client information</li><li>Customer-focused mindset with a natural service orientation</li></ul><p>Location</p><ul><li>Central Singapore (office-based / administrative role)</li></ul><p>Why Join Heartland Rehab</p><ul><li>Meaningful work in healthcare</li><li>Clear systems and support</li><li>Training provided</li><li>Exposure to a growing multi-clinic organisation</li><li>Stable role with growth opportunities</li></ul><p>To apply, please send your application to 📩 info@heartlandrehab.sg</p>",
